- for.gen

This example shows the different usages of the `@loop` directive.

@run {
    # For can be used to iterate over any iterable
    @for i in [1, 5, 3] {
        i
    }
    \n

    # If an integer is provided, it will iterate from 0 to n-1
    @for i in 3 {
        i
    }
    \n

    # If you need to track the index:
    @for idx, val in ['a', 'b', 'c'] {
        f"idx: {idx}, val: {val}"   \n
    }
}

Example output:
1 5 3 
0 1 2 
idx: 0, val: a
idx: 1, val: b
idx: 2, val: c
